The medical students get aware in the main environmental and occupational risk factors and their health impact; the students learn the main occupational risks in medicine; the students have the basic knowledge of environmental risk assessment; The subject pay attention on the need of diagnostics of environmental and occupational diseases in the future clinical practice; The students get aware in coping and prevention methods of environmental health risks.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce the main risk factors in living and work environment; to learn environmental health impact assessment and prevention of diseases caused by environmental and occupational risk factors.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  1. The medical students get acquired in the main health risks in environmental and occupational risks and ambient environment related to air, soil, drinking water, food and waste management. 
2. The students get aware in the main occupational risks in medicine. 
3. The students have knowledge in basics of health impact assessment. 
4. The students can use this knowledge in early diagnostics of environmental and occupational diseases.
5. The students know the methods of prevention.
